<paragraph blockId="6.[136,1452,338,580]" pageId="6" pageNumber="25">
Perennial plant with non flowering shoots creeping and rooting, densely leafy for lanceolated and glaucous leaves. Flowering stem erect, 
<quantity box="[484,602,446,473]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.25" metricValueMax="4.5" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="6" pageNumber="25" unit="cm" value="32.5" valueMax="45.0" valueMin="20.0">20–45 cm</quantity>
, inflorescence erect before the anthesis, somewhat scorpioid, glabrous or glandular, bracteate; flowers (5) 6 (7) merous, obdiplostemonous, with triangular-lanceolated sepals (
<quantity box="[1296,1394,482,508]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" metricValueMax="4.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="6" pageNumber="25" unit="mm" value="3.5" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="3.0">3–4 mm</quantity>
) and petals spreading or semi-erect, yellow lemon; filaments yellow, papillose at their bases, styles slightly outwards at the anthesis.
</paragraph>
